      <sec id="S5">
        <title>Lentiviral shRNAs</title>
        <p id="P17">All shRNA targeting sequences were cloned into DECIPHERâ¢ pRSI9-U6-(sh)-UbiC-TagRFP-2A-Puro (Cellecta, CA). shRNA targeting sequences listed below were based on RNAi consortium at Broad Institute (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://www.broad.mit.edu/rnai/trc">http://www.broad.mit.edu/rnai/trc</ext-link>). YTHDF2 (mouse): 5â²-GCTCCAGGCATGAATACTATA-3â²; FTO (mouse): 5â²-GCTGAGGCAGTTCTGGTTTCA 3â²; Scramble control sequence: 5â²-AACAGTCGCGTTTGCGACTGG-3â². Lentiviral particles were packaged using Lenti-X 293T cells (Clontech). Virus-containing supernatants were collected at 48-h after transfection and filtered to eliminate cells. MEF cells were infected by the lentivirus for 48 hr before selection by 1 Î¼g ml<sup>-1</sup> puromycin.</p>
      </sec>
      <sec id="S6">
